values:
whats up. pretty uneventful day. i walked down to the marina and checked out that frank gehry fish building. walked back and slept. i woke up and giev was there. we went to leave and kyan was there. should i go out tonight? i dunno. we gotta be outta the hostel by noon, and we got the train to catch. i think i may play it safe and stay in tonight. even though its our last night in barcelona. well see. were gonna go get some chow and look for luggage that wont kill our shoulders. then we gotta meet up with marcos at 10.

giev and kyan are already talking about drinking absinth tonight. be afraid. im gonna go on record and say that i will never touch the stuff again. good ol budweiser for me--or estrella damm, the local beer.

whats up people
so, im in chicago. for work. but technically its traveling so i figured id post a lil thingy.
pretty cool city. puts fort lauderdale to shame--thats for sure. im in an apple store right now, checkin my email and all that good stuff. its amazing how many transients are in here just for the free internet use. i told my boss about it and he got all excited too--i think hes gonna come over here to do the same.

a cop on a segway just rolled past me. he he.

okay--its my last night here. im gonna go down to rush street and get drunk.

okay, so a few of us are taking a trip to spain this summer. one of my friends is already there--and im gonna meet him out there at the end of the month.

rather than write emails to everyone individually at cybercafes where i gotta pay by the hour to write 'em (the euro is kicking our ass) i am just going to post here--at the live journal. just click and youll be able to see whats going on with me.

so, since im still here theres nothing to write about--check back at the end of the month.
